    "SubstructuresBoth internal and external boards could have substructures.",
    "Certain responsibilities could be delegated to a part of the ethics board.Two common substructures are committees and liaisons.",
    "(Note that an internal ethics board can be a committee of the company, but the ethics board can also have committees.)",
    "Committees could be permanent (for recurring responsibilities) or temporary (to address one-time issues).",
    "For example, the board could have a permanent \"deployment committee\" that reviews model releases, or it could have a temporary committee for advising the board on an upcoming M&A transaction."
